Installation
Step 1: 
Install EPICS base and recommended packages. See below link:
http://epics.nsls2.bnl.gov/debian/

Install Python 2.7: sudo apt-get install python-2.7

Install Python-dev: sudo apt-get install python-dev

Install Ipython: sudo apt-get install ipython

Install Python-Requests: sudo apt-get install python-requests


Step 2:  
Clone pyBL git repository to your HOME directory from: https://github.com/arkilic/pyBL/

Step 3:
 Inside pyBL/motorSim folder: 
$ make clean
$make install

Step 4: 
Confirm virtual motors are installed properly. Inside motorSim folder:
$./startSimMotorEdm.sh
$./startSimMotor.sh
Once both of these commands are performed, an edm window must show up displaying current motor positions. 

Step 5: 
Inside $HOME/pyBL/:
$sudo make install

Configuration:
Once installed, for any new configuration to take affect, you have to repeat Step 5 above.

Step 1:
Add diffcalc repository to PYTHONPATH.Inside pyBL:

Step 1: 
Run the program:
$cd $HOME/pyBL/
$./runPyBL

Step 3:
Inside pyBL.conf modify configuration parameters for startup:
[diffractometer_config]
name=X11
geometry=SixCircle
engine=you
tag=default_tag
author=pyBL
pv1=test:mtr1
pv2=test:mtr2
pv3=test:mtr3
pv4=test:mtr4
pv5=test:mtr5
pv6=test:mtr6

